    "caption": "The real mermaid — gentle, grey, and munching seagrass.",
    "shortDescription": "Dugongs are the sea cows of the Indian Ocean and Pacific, grazing on underwater meadows of seagrass the way a cow grazes on a field. Ancient sailors who spotted them from a distance thought they were mermaids — and you can sort of see why, from far away with bad eyesight. Fun fact: Dugongs are the only marine mammals that eat almost nothing but plants."
